-- Boston Properties Agrees to Purchase John Hancock Tower for $930 Million
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2010-10-04T13:20:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/boston-properties-agrees-to-purchase-john-hancock-tower-for-930-million.html
Boston Properties Inc. said it has
entered into an agreement to acquire the John Hancock Tower and
Garage in Boston, Massachussetts for an aggregate purchase price
of about $930 million.  The seller is a joint venture between an affiliate of
Normandy Real Estate Partners and an affiliate of Five Mile
Capital Partners. The closing is expected to occur in the fourth
quarter of 2010.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  